The Commissioner shall take action under subsection (b) of this section if, on investigation, the Commissioner finds that a domestic society:
has exceeded its powers;
has failed to comply with this subtitle;
is not fulfilling its contracts in good faith;
has a membership of less than 400 after an existence of 1 year or more;
is conducting its insurance business fraudulently; or
is conducting its insurance business in a manner hazardous to its members, creditors, the public, or the business.

A society enjoined from conducting insurance business under this section may not conduct insurance business until:
the Commissioner finds that the violation has been corrected;
the costs of the action have been paid by the society, if the court finds that the society was in default;
the court has dissolved the injunction; and
the Commissioner has reinstated the society's certificate of authority.
